Class
Description
BinaryExample
Example of the Progenitor genetic algorithm using BinaryGene whose goal it is to create a Chromosome of 100 binary genes with all values being "1".
BinaryGene
Implementation of a Gene with a binary value
CharacterExample
Example of the Progenitor genetic algorithm using CharacterValueGene whose goal it is to create a predefined string.
CharacterValueGene
Implementation of a Gene with Character values
Chromosome
Representation of a chromosome containing Genes
CrossoverMethod
Crossover method determines how a new Chromosome is created from two parents Chromosomes.
EndCondition
End condition determines when the execution of the generic algorithm stops.
Gene<T>
Base implementation of a gene.
IntegerExample
Example of the Progenitor genetic algorithm using IntegerValueGene whose goal it is to create a Chromosome of 100 numbers between 1 and 100 with the highest total value
IntegerValueGene
Implementation of a Gene with Integer values within a user-defined range
NumericValueGene<T extends Comparable>
Base implementation of a numeric value gene with user-defined bounds

Implementation of the Genetic algorithm, containing a Builder Pattern with default values, implementations of selection methods, crossovers, and mutation
Progenitor.Builder
Builder pattern for the genetic algorithm containing default values
Rand
Singleton class for generating random values, used to avoid creation of multiple Rand objects
RunNotCompletedException
Thrown when a post-run parameter is requested from the Progenitor class before a run has been executed.
SelectionMethod
Selection method determines the logic for selecting a parent chromosome
ValueGene<T extends Comparable>
Base implementation of a value gene
ValueOutOfBoundsException
Thrown when attempting to create a gene with a value outside its defined bounds
